dct_title_s: Map of routes for a Pacific railroad
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Appears in the U.S. War Dept.'s Report of the Secretary of War on the several Pacific railroad explorations, 1855. "This is a hurried compilation of all the authentic surveys and is designed to exhibit the relations of the different routes to each other. An elaborate map on scale of 1:3,000,000 is being compiled and is in an advanced state."
dct_publisher_sm: [Washington, D.C.] : Office of P. R. R. Surveys, 1855 (N[ew] Y[ork] : Lith. of Bien & Sterner)
